Eclipse is open with the workspace at /home/user/workspace.

Create TWO related Java projects in this workspace where 'UtilsConsumer' depends on 'CommonUtils' via an Eclipse project reference:

1. Java project 'CommonUtils' (Java nature, default 'src' source folder) with src/common/StringUtils.java:

```
package common;

public class StringUtils {
    public static String reverse(String s) {
        return new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
    }
}
```

2. Java project 'UtilsConsumer' (Java nature, default 'src' source folder) with src/app/ConsumerMain.java:

```
package app;

import common.StringUtils;

public class ConsumerMain {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(StringUtils.reverse("hello"));
    }
}
```

3. Add 'CommonUtils' to the Java build path of 'UtilsConsumer' as a required project — the resulting .classpath of 'UtilsConsumer' must contain a classpathentry of kind 'src' with path `/CommonUtils`.

Both projects must compile successfully.
